# Kubernetes Manifests for DevOpsify E-Commerce App

This directory will contain the necessary Kubernetes manifest files to deploy the frontend, backend, and database components of the e-commerce application. Below are the sample contents for the Kubernetes manifests.

### 1. frontend-deployment.yaml

apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: frontend
  labels:
    app: devopsify-frontend
spec:
  replicas: 2
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: devopsify-frontend
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: devopsify-frontend
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: frontend
        image: <your-dockerhub-username>/devopsify-frontend:latest
        ports:
        - containerPort: 3000
        env:
        - name: API_URL
          value: "http://backend:5000"

---

### 2. frontend-service.yaml

apiVersion: v1
kind: Service
metadata:
  name: frontend
spec:
  type: LoadBalancer
  ports:
  - port: 80
    targetPort: 3000
  selector:
    app: devopsify-frontend

---

### 3. backend-deployment.yaml

apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: backend
  labels:
    app: devopsify-backend
spec:
  replicas: 2
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: devopsify-backend
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: devopsify-backend
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: backend
        image: <your-dockerhub-username>/devopsify-backend:latest
        ports:
        - containerPort: 5000
        env:
        - name: DATABASE_URL
          value: "postgres://<username>:<password>@postgresql:5432/devopsify"

---

### 4. backend-service.yaml

apiVersion: v1
kind: Service
metadata:
  name: backend
spec:
  ports:
  - port: 5000
    targetPort: 5000
  selector:
    app: devopsify-backend

---

### 5. postgresql-deployment.yaml

apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: postgresql
  labels:
    app: devopsify-postgresql
spec:
  replicas: 1
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: devopsify-postgresql
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: devopsify-postgresql
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: postgresql
        image: postgres:latest
        ports:
        - containerPort: 5432
        env:
        - name: POSTGRES_USER
          value: "<username>"
        - name: POSTGRES_PASSWORD
          value: "<password>"
        - name: POSTGRES_DB
          value: "devopsify"

---

### 6. postgresql-service.yaml

apiVersion: v1
kind: Service
metadata:
  name: postgresql
spec:
  ports:
  - port: 5432
    targetPort: 5432
  selector:
    app: devopsify-postgresql

---

### 7. redis-deployment.yaml (Optional)

apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: redis
  labels:
    app: devopsify-redis
spec:
  replicas: 1
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: devopsify-redis
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: devopsify-redis
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: redis
        image: redis:latest
        ports:
        - containerPort: 6379

---

### 8. redis-service.yaml (Optional)

apiVersion: v1
kind: Service
metadata:
  name: redis
spec:
  ports:
  - port: 6379
    targetPort: 6379
  selector:
    app: devopsify-redis

---

These manifest files will allow you to deploy the frontend, backend, PostgreSQL, and optionally Redis services to your Kubernetes cluster. Make sure to replace `<your-dockerhub-username>`, `<username>`, and `<password>` with your actual values.